tnerships"],"qualification_notes":"Good fit — unique multi-vendor GPU infrastructure, active deployment at scale. No identified CFO/finance lead — David Driggers is CEO/CTO combo, likely handles major financial decisions. Acquisition by BOXX means there''s a parent company finance structure to navigate. Residual value coverage conversation may need to go through BOXX."}', '2026-03-21 02:49:33');
INSERT OR IGNORE INTO research_notes (id, company_id, source_url, summary, raw_data, created_at) VALUES ('daf7e959-4e3c-48bc-bbf8-8c8199a90e9f', '22530fe7-5fc8-4a56-8df0-8b57774cfda5', 'https://tensorwave.com', 'Strong fit — AMD-focused neocloud with large GPU fleet and fresh capital. No debt identified beyond equity rounds. Magnetar Capital involvement is interesting — they''re a sophisticated credit investor. 40-person team scaling to 100+ means finance function is still lean. COO Piotr Tomasik likely handles operational finance. No dedicated CFO identified — worth checking.

GPU scale: 8,000 AMD Instinct MI325X GPUs in dedicated training cluster. Liquid-cooled. Building world''s largest liquid-cooled AMD GPU deployment. Run-rate revenue target: $100M+ by end of 2025 (20x YoY).

Funding: October 2024: $43M SAFE led by Nexus VP. May 2025: $100M Series A led by Magnetar and AMD Ventures. Total raised: $146.7M.

Financing: $100M Series A (May 2025) — used for AMD GPU cluster expansion. Magnetar, AMD Ventures, Maverick Silicon, Nexus VP, Prosperity7.

Partners: AMD (preferred cloud partner), Magnetar Capital, Nexus Venture Partners, AMD Ventures

Recent news:
• May 2025: $100M Series A co-led by Magnetar and AMD Ventures to build 8,000+ AMD GPU cluster
• October 2024: $43M SAFE (largest in Nevada startup history)
• 2025: Deployed 8,000 AMD MI325X GPUs as dedicated training cluster
